headline: Nasdaq Funds Miss Out on Oracle Rally
summary: Investors in popular tech-heavy index funds like Invesco's QQQ might be surprised to learn they aren't benefiting from Oracle's surge to a near trillion dollar market value on Wednesday. That's because Larry Ellison's company moved its listing from the Nasdaq to the New York Stock Exchange back in 2013, marking the largest ever defection from either exchange.
